                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/34908",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Closing as 'incomplete' as for it's unclear (read: real vague) what is asked for here.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-09-25T08:53:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-09-25T08:53:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44253",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fenoms",
                        "name": "fenoms",
                        "displayName": "Pawel Szczekutowicz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think this was about ability to add in config file (application.ini) something like this:\r\n\r\nresources.locale.cache = \"\"locale\"\r\n\r\nand this cache named \"locale\" can be defined by\/in cachemanager also using config file (application.ini)\r\n\r\nresources.cachemanager.locale.frontend.name = Core\r\netc...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fenoms",
                        "name": "fenoms",
                        "displayName": "Pawel Szczekutowicz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-03T06:22:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-03T06:22:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44256",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fenoms",
                        "name": "fenoms",
                        "displayName": "Pawel Szczekutowicz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This patch should give the desired functionality\r\n\r\n*** library\/Zend\/Application\/Resource\/Locale.php\t2010-02-01 21:13:08.000000000 +0100\r\n--- library\/Zend\/Application\/Resource\/Locale.php\t2011-02-03 15:33:05.375000092 +0100\r\n***************\r\n*** 86,89 ****\r\n--- 86,121 ----\r\n  \r\n          return $this->_locale;\r\n      }\r\n+     \r\n+    \/**\r\n+      * Set the locale cache\r\n+      *\r\n+      * @param string|Zend_Cache_Core $cache\r\n+      * @return Zend_Application_Resource_Locale\r\n+      *\/\r\n+     public function setCache($cache)\r\n+     {\r\n+         $localeCache = null;\r\n+ \r\n+         if (is_string($cache)) {\r\n+             $bootstrap = $this->getBootstrap();\r\n+             if ($bootstrap instanceof Zend_Application_Bootstrap_ResourceBootstrapper\r\n+                 && $bootstrap->hasPluginResource('CacheManager')\r\n+             ) {\r\n+                 $cacheManager = $bootstrap->bootstrap('CacheManager')\r\n+                     ->getResource('CacheManager');\r\n+                 if (null !== $cacheManager && $cacheManager->hasCache($cache)) {\r\n+                     $localeCache = $cacheManager->getCache($cache);\r\n+                 }\r\n+             }\r\n+         } else if ($cache instanceof Zend_Cache_Core) {\r\n+             $localeCache = $cache;\r\n+         }\r\n+ \r\n+         if ($localeCache instanceof Zend_Cache_Core) {\r\n+             Zend_Locale::setCache($localeCache);\r\n+         }\r\n+ \r\n+         return $this;\r\n+     }    \r\n  }\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=fenoms",
                        "name": "fenoms",
                        "displayName": "Pawel Szczekutowicz",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-03T08:43:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-03T08:43:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44257",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hujuice",
                        "name": "hujuice",
                        "displayName": "Sergio Vaccaro",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "See the alternative proposed at [10720|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/browse\/ZF-10720].\r\nThe way that I suggested (not as patch for laziness) gives the opportunity to use a more generally available cache:\r\n{code:title=application.ini}\r\n; ...\r\nresources.cachemanager.myCache.frontend.name = Core\r\n...\r\nresources.locale.cache = \"myCache\"\r\n; ...\r\n{code} \r\n\r\nI think that a 'merge' between the two solutions should be used.\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\nSergio\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=hujuice",
                        "name": "hujuice",
                        "displayName": "Sergio Vaccaro",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-03T10:00:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-03T10:00:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44260",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=intiilapa",
                        "name": "intiilapa",
                        "displayName": "Beno\u00eet Durand",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Pawe? Szczekutowicz, we can not use a patch if you have not signed CLA.\r\n\r\nI will follow the code I made for other resources (#ZF-10033, #ZF-10034, and #ZF-10049). I forgot that Zend_Locale also had a cache too.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=intiilapa",
                        "name": "intiilapa",
                        "displayName": "Beno\u00eet Durand",
